@prusnak 

`python` seems to be test-only dep, so it's not necessary to build a `bitcoind` binary

`libevent` is one of the `base` and `systemd` deps so everyone has it

@laanwj I agree, but I'm not sure if it belongs to Arch section. This note might help someone build Bitcoin Core with incompatible legacy DB, which is still problematic

There is a separate section which explains how to include compatible `bdb`, and it seems to be the recommended approach: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/build-unix.md#berkeley-db

If the concern is that people might miss this section, maybe it worth adding a link to it instead of repeating similar recipes in every distribution-specific section
